    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nmodelines are insecure. \n\n### Expected behavior\n\nRather than yet another option/whitelist (e.g. https://github.com/vim/vim/pull/19875 ), leverage the `:trust` mechanism.\n\n- When a modeline is detected, prompt the user if it's not in the trust database. \n- User can either trust the file or the \"workspace\".\n    - If the file is in CWD then the \"workspace\" is CWD.\n    - If the file is outside of CWD, the \"workspace\" is the file's parent dir?\n\n```\nmodeline found in file foo/bar.txt\nTrust this file? (Y)es / (N)o / Workspace (d)irectory\n```\n\nmodelines are added to the trust db as follows:\n\n- hash only the *modeline contents*, not the entire file contents",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Unsure about requiring `:trust` for *all* modelines. Modelines are a rather common occurrence, which can lead to warning fatigue and unnecessary friction, especially when most modelines set harmless options that could also be set by an editorconfig file (without prompting).\n\nI recommend we create a whitelist of safe options, and then only prompt for `:trust` if a modeline contains an option that isn't in the whitelist.",
