        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "'filetype' triggers ftplugins, which have a big surface area. Thus even if modeline is carefully \"whitelisted\", as long as things like 'filetype' are allowed, there is a lot of room for security holes. For example, if a ftplugin invokes `system()`, a malicious filename placed in the right location can invoke shell code. And this has happened more than once.\n\nAnd that's why https://github.com/vim/vim/pull/19875 is just a complete waste of time.",
