            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> we just need to do a security scan of all the builtin ftplugins?\n\nmm, the AIs are doing that for us 😂  and we have merged fixes from vim (thanks to @zeertzjq )\n\nI agree that modeline itself is not too interesting, but continuing to develop it and build scar-tissue around it is even less interesting. Instead we should leverage the trust mechanism for all kinds of \"environment-specific auto-execution\", of which modeline is one such case.",
