            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Disclaimer: I don't use modelines. I don't use `:sandbox`.\n\nMy 2cents on modelines in a developer tool is all-or-nothing.\n\n0. Security configuration is up-front on (post)installation.\n1. Avoid/reduce user configuration on security-sensitive options.\n   modeline cannot modify the editor's behavior regarding security.\n2. `set modeline modelineexpr nomodelinestrict` go together. Keeping track of applicable options for modelineexpr and now modelinestrict is a chore. \n3. Use modeline only on trusted files/directories. By default, do not trust any file/directory, not even the (neo)vim repository.\n    If possible, setup `exrc` and local trust file for the repository.\n    `:trust` can be updated to accept a local trust file to auto-trust all listed files/directories (non-recursive).\n    Security risk at price of convenience.\n    If possible, setup nvim's trust file to whitelist nvim's `runtime/` so it can distrust everything by default.\n\nI'd rather pursue a permission model and strict mode cli flag on startup.",
